Who's killing the great bears of Montana?
The Bush administration on Tuesday is to take the
first step toward removing Yellowstone's grizzly bears, a living icon
of the American West, from the nation's endangered species list.
A nine-year study coinciding with burgeoning development in and around Banff
National Park has found the area's grizzly bears have the lowest reproductive
rate ever recorded in North America, scientists at the University of Calgary
said.